main event: A round, white object was observed by the USAF Radar Crew 6 miles SE of Lompoc, California in October 1957.
interesting points: The object was determined to be Venus, approximately 30 degrees above the horizon at the time of sighting.
Intermittent white light is observed if the weather is clear at dusk.
No movement was observed for the object during the sighting.
The observation was made by a civilian student, 18 years old, in Santa Maria, California.
